  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen. This was the sign or token; See Gill on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 16:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The subscription to this epistle is, \"The Second Epistle to the Thessalonians was written from Athens\"; though it seems rather to be written from Corinth. In the Syriac version it is said, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"the Second Epistle to the Thessalonians, which is written from Laodicea of Pisidia, and sent by the hands of Tychicus.'' ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "\"the Second Epistle to the Thessalonians, which is written from Laodicea of Pisidia, and sent by the hands of Tychicus.'' ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
